# Module 1.3: Review (Module 1 Wrap-Up)

## Overview

This section summarizes the key concepts covered in Module 1 and reinforces the foundational knowledge required to understand cybersecurity principles.

## Glossary Highlights

Important terms to remember:

- Threat  
- Vulnerability  
- Risk  
- Phishing  
- Malware  
- Incident  

## Module 1 Challenge

By the end of this module, you should be able to:

- Define cybersecurity  
- Explain why cybersecurity is important  
- Identify common cyber threats, especially phishing  
- Understand different roles in cybersecurity  
- Recognize the core skills required in the field  

## Key Takeaways

- Cybersecurity protects systems, networks, and data  
- Threats exploit vulnerabilities, creating risk  
- Entry-level analysts monitor and respond to threats  
- Both technical and soft skills are essential for success  

## Big Picture

Cybersecurity is not only about technology. It is about protecting people, organizations, and information in an increasingly digital world.
